# write a function rectangle_area(with, height) that takes the with and height of a rectangle as input and returns its area.

def rectangle_area (width, height):
    area= width*height
    return f"the area of a rectangle with width {width} and height {height} is {area}"

def central_difference(f, x, h):
    derivative= (f(x+h)- f(x-h))/ (2*h)
    return derivative
